text_blocks.content: 1 Instruction No. 27: Count Six: Sex Trafficking of an Individual Under the Age of 18a Minor - Second Element

The second element of Count Six which the Government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that Ms. Maxwell knew that Carolyn was under eighteen years of age. In considering whether Ms. Maxwell knew that Carolyn had not attained the age of eighteen, please apply the definition of "knowingly" previously provided to you.
